Package: boundid
Title: Test and adjust for boundary bias in difference-in-differences designs.
Version: 0.0.0.91
Authors@R: 
    person("Ludwig", "Schulze", , "ludwig.schulze@eui.eu", role = c("aut", "cre"))
    person("Joris", "Frese", , "joris.frese@eui.eu", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-5871-997X"))
Description: This packages accompanies the article "Going Through the Roof: Difference-in-Differences Designs in Contexts of Natural Boundaries" 
             by Ludwig Schulze and Joris Frese. It contains functions to detect and adjust for parallel trend violations in difference-in-differences 
             estimations due to natural boundaries in the outcome variable. See the README for a more detailed description and a working example.
